ide.backend.model.variables

Class AbstractRefVariabelModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Observable
      • ide.backend.model.BlockModel
        • ide.backend.model.variables.AbstractRefVariabelModel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    Direct Known Subclasses:
    RefMemberModel, RefVariabelModel

    public abstract class AbstractRefVariabelModel
extends BlockModel
implements java.util.Observer
    This class represents the common base for references to variables (RefMemberModel and RefVariableModel) Common functions are defined in this class. This class is abstract.
    Author:
    Matthijs Kaminski

      • tellParentChanged

        public void tellParentChanged(BlockModel child,
                              Variable.VariableType type)
        Description copied from class: BlockModel
        If the parent of a block that its changed so that typechecking or other error detection can be preformed. This is an upwards chain in the tree if models. If this function is not relevant the block can stop the chain by not calling his parent.
        Specified by:
        tellParentChanged in class BlockModel
        Parameters:
        child - child calling this function
        type - type of variable of the child.
